  title `Short title.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00051_198348_1517807326456&sectionId=32528&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00051_198348_1517807326456
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `This Act may be called the Public Financial Institutions (Obligation as to Fidelity and`
  line `Secrecy) Act, 1983.`
obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (32529)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title Definitions.
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00051_198348_1517807326456&sectionId=32529&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00051_198348_1517807326456
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `(1) In this Act, "public financial institution" means--`
  line
  line `(a) the Industrial Credit and Investment Corporation of India Limited, a company formed and`
  line `registered under the Indian Companies Act, 1913(7 of 1913);`
  line
  line `(b) the Industrial Reconstruction Corporation of India Limited, a company formed and registered`
  line `under the Companies Act, 1956(1 of 1956); or`
  line
  line `(c) any other institution, being a company as defined in section 617 of the Companies Act,`
  line `1956(1 of 1956) or a company to which the provisions of section 619 of that Act apply, which the`
  line `Central Government may, having regard to the nature of the business carried on by such institution,`
  line `by notification in the Official Gazette, specify to be a public financial institution for the purposes of`
  line `this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) Every notification issued under clause (c) of sub-section (1) shall, as soon as may be, after it is`
  line `issued, be laid before each House of Parliament.`
obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (32530)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title `Obligation as to fidelity and secrecy.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 30 of 2005, s. 34 and the Schedule (w.e.f. 14-12-2006).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00051_198348_1517807326456&sectionId=32530&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00051_198348_1517807326456
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `(1) A public financial institution shall not, except as`
  line `otherwise provided in sub-section (2) or in any other law for the time being in force, divulge any`
  line `information relating to, or to the affairs of, its constituents except in circumstances in which it is, in`
  line `accordance with the law or practice and usage, customary among bankers, necessary or appropriate for`
  line `the public financial institution to divulge such information.`
  line
  line `(2) A public financial institution may, for the purpose of efficient discharge of its functions, collect`
  line `from, or furnish to,--`
  line
  line `(a) the Central Government; or`
  line
  line `(b) the State Bank of India constituted under section 3 of the State Bank of India Act, 1955(23 of`
  line `1955), any subsidiary bank within the meaning of the State Bank of India (Subsidiary Banks) Act,`
  line `1959(38 of 1959), any corresponding new bank constituted under section 3 of the Banking`
  line `Companies (Acquisition and Transfer of Undertakings) Act, 1970(5 of 1970) or under section 3 of the`
  line `Banking Companies (Acquisition and Transfer of Undertakings) Act, 1980 (40 of 1980), any other`
  line `scheduled bank within the meaning of the Reserve Bank of India Act, 1934(2 of 1934); or`
  line
  line `(c) any other public financial institution,`
  line
  line `such credit information or other information as it may consider useful for the purpose, in such manner and`
  line `at such time as it may think fit.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purposes of this sub-section, the expression "credit information" shall have the`
  line `same meaning as in clause (c) of section 45A of the Reserve Bank of India Act, 1934 (2 of 1934) subject`
  line `to the modification that the banking company referred to therein shall mean a bank referred to in clause`
  line `(b) of this sub-section or a public financial institution.`
  line
  line `^1[(3) Nothing contained in this section shall apply to the credit information disclosed under the Credit`
  line `Information Companies (Regulation) Act, 2005 (30 of 2005).]`
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (32531)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 4
  title `Declaration of fidelity and secrecy.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00051_198348_1517807326456&sectionId=32531&sectionno=4&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00051_198348_1517807326456
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `Every director, member of any committee, auditor or`
  line `officer or any other employee of a public financial institution to which this Act applies, shall,--`
  line
  line `(a) before entering upon his duties; or`
  line
  line `(b) where he has entered upon his duties as such before the date on which this Act became`
  line `applicable to such institution, within thirty days from the date on which this Act became applicable to`
  line `such institution,`
  line
  line `make a declaration of fidelity and secrecy in the form set out in the Schedule to this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes:
  string
  line
